## 🚀 How to Run
1. Create a new RTL project in your SystemVerilog-compatible simulation tool (e.g., Vivado).
2. Add the design code containing `bcd_adder`, `RIPPLE_CARRY_ADDER`, and `fulladder` as your design sources.
3. Add the simulation code containing `bcd_adder_if` and `bcd_adder_tb` as your simulation sources. (Make sure this file has a `.sv` extension).
4. Set `bcd_adder_tb` as the top module for simulation.
5. Run the behavioral simulation and open the waveform viewer.
6. Add the interface signals (`vif.a`, `vif.b`, `vif.c`, `vif.sum`, `vif.cout`) to the wave window to observe the timing transitions.

